this graduate student faq is a resource for current and new graduate students at sjsu. its six sections, " general ", " admissions ", " academic planning/ enrollment ", " advancement to candidacy ", " jobs/internships ", and " culminating experience " are meant to serve as an easy-to-use guide to answer common questions. also refer graduate student handbook for information regarding campus life, wellness, open university and special sessions. general admissions conditional classification refers to your admission standing at sjsu and means that you have not satisfied all the required conditions for admission. the gape office provides you a letter which specifies the conditions being placed on your admission. you are not allowed to take more than 12 units of graduate courses until the conditions are satisfied. after you have satisfied all of the required conditions, you will need to fill out a change of classification in graduate program form [pdf] [pdf] and submit to your graduate program advisor to change your status. classified status indicates that you have satisfied all of the conditions of admission. it depends on the program you are applying to. please check the gape website for test requirements by college and program here . conditional admission requires that your conditions are satisfied. if you have any prior coursework that might be similar and/or have any questions about your conditions, please contact your program advisor to receive guidance. tuition fees and other fees for graduate students can be found under the bursar's office website . for questions about admission deferral to a graduate program, please check this webpage by the admissions' office. check out the steps to enrollment and who to contact if you have questions here . yes, it is currently called ms in quality assurance, but there is plan to rename it to ms in engineering technology in the near future. academic planning/ enrollment advancement to candidacy you may obtain the candidacy form from the gape forms site . you will need to be in classified status in your program, have earned at least 9 units of letter-graded courses, have fulfilled the gwar, and be in good standing to file your advancement to candidacy petition . you will need to file a request for course substitution to substitute a core or an elective course listed on the candidacy form. you can find this online request under forms on the gape website. jobs/internships internship work during the fall and spring semesters is limited to 20 hours per week maximum for international students via the curricular practical training (cpt) program. full-time work hours are possible while on cpt during the summer term. if you have completed all your program coursework except your culminating experience, talk to an isss advisor to see if you are eligible for and interested in early option post-opt or pre-opt. full-time work for international students on cpt is allowed during the summer term. you can also work on campus during that time of the year if your schedule allows. check with an isss advisor if you have specific circumstances to consult on.  culminating experience your culminating experience is a project or a thesis at the graduate level. a culminating experience form is required by the university to show that you have met the necessary skills to obtain an ms degree. the form is processed by the graduate advisor after you have passed the project or thesis course successfully and your final report has been approved by your graduate committee. please reach out to your program advisor /department mailbox for program specific questions. monday through friday, during business hours (closed weekends and holidays) visit office: virtually or in person at eng 116 undergraduate: success-engineering@sjsu.edu graduate: graduate-engineering@sjsu.edu appointments with advisors: spartan connect phone: 408-924-3990 all online courses at sjsu are delivered through canvas . monday through friday (except weekends and holidays), hours depending on location. : see our calendar for virtual/drop-in hours : engineering 1st floor eng 116 monday through friday 8:30 a.m. to 12:00 noon 1:00 p.m. to 4:30 p.m. (closed for lunch daily 12:00 - 1:00) in-person drop-in calendar san josé state university one washington square, san josé, ca 95192-0220 